import Frontier.Issue4Pesin.ManeLowerBound
import Mathlib.Probability.Martingale.Convergence

/-!
# Pesin part 2, node N-L1-RN: the Layer-1 conditional-density martingale step (foliation-free)

This file isolates and proves **sorry-free** the abstract measure-theoretic core of the one
sub-step of Ma√Ī√©'s Proposition 7.7 that the recon flagged as node `N-L1-RN`: the convergence,
and sub-exponential-rate decay, of the **conditional-density martingale** `r_n := őľ(P‚āô)/őĹ(P‚āô)`.

## What N-L1-RN actually is, and what it does NOT need

In Ma√Ī√©'s proof (Contractor *The Pesin Entropy Formula*, ¬ß7, Prop. 7.7) the only place a martingale
enters is the splitting
`(1/n) log őľ(P‚āô(x)) = (1/n) log őĹ(P‚āô(x)) + (1/n) log (őľ(P‚āô(x)) / őĹ(P‚āô(x)))`,
whose **last term tends to `0` a.e.** The ratio `r_n(x) = őľ(P‚āô(x))/őĹ(P‚āô(x))` is, atom by atom along
the refining partition `P‚āô`, exactly the value of the conditional expectation of the
Radon‚ÄďNikodym density `g := dőľ/dőĹ` with respect to the ŌÉ-algebra `‚ĄĪ n` generated by `P‚āô`:
`r_n(x) = (őĹ[g | ‚ĄĪ n]) x`. By the a.e. L√©vy upward / L¬Ļ-martingale-convergence theorem
(`MeasureTheory.Integrable.tendsto_ae_condExp`) this converges a.e. to the `‚ĄĪ_‚ąě`-measurable
`g = dőľ/dőĹ`, a finite limit; where `g > 0` the real-analytic tail
`rate_log_div_tendsto_zero_of_tendsto_pos` (already landed in `ManeLowerBound`) sends
`(1/n) log r_n ‚Üí 0`.

**The decisive observation: this martingale step is purely measure-theoretic.** It refers only to a
filtration `‚ĄĪ : Filtration ‚Ąē m0` on the ambient measurable space, an integrable density
`g : ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ`, and the conditional expectations `őĹ[g | ‚ĄĪ n]`. It needs **no foliation, no leaf
measure `őĹ` as a geometric object, no unstable manifold `P‚āô`** ‚ÄĒ the partition's only role is to
*generate* the abstract filtration `‚ĄĪ`, and the leaf measure's only role is to be the *base*
measure against which `g = dőľ/dőĹ` and the conditional expectations are taken. Thus N-L1-RN admits a
faithful, fully general statement that this file lands sorry-free. A future SMB/Ma√Ī√© proof
consumes `condDensity_log_rate_tendsto_zero` directly, supplying `‚ĄĪ` = (partition-generated
filtration), the base measure = leaf volume `őĹ`, and `g` = `dőľ/dőĹ`.

## Main results

* `condExp_tendsto_ae` ‚ÄĒ the bare a.e. martingale convergence of the conditional-density sequence
  `(őĹ[g | ‚ĄĪ n]) x ‚Üí g x`, a direct specialisation of `Integrable.tendsto_ae_condExp`. This is the
  martingale half of N-L1-RN.
* `condDensity_log_rate_tendsto_zero` ‚ÄĒ **the full N-L1-RN building block**: for an integrable,
  `‚ĄĪ_‚ąě`-measurable, a.e.-strictly-positive density `g`, the log conditional-density rate vanishes,
  `(1/n) ¬∑ log ((őĹ[g | ‚ĄĪ n]) x) ‚Üí 0` for a.e. `x`. This is exactly the term Ma√Ī√© discards; it is
  the composition of the martingale convergence above with the already-landed real-analytic tail
  `rate_log_div_tendsto_zero_of_tendsto_pos`.

Both are sorry-free and axiom-clean (`propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound`).

## What remains BLOCKED (and is *not* this node)

Wiring this into Prop. 7.7 still needs: the countable refining partition `P‚āô` whose generated
filtration is `‚ĄĪ` (with `diam P‚āô ‚Č§ ŌĀ`), the identification `r_n = őĹ[dőľ/dőĹ | ‚ĄĪ n]` atom-by-atom, the
leaf measure `őĹ` as a geometric object (the unstable foliation / Pesin manifold theorem), and the
Shannon‚ÄďMcMillan‚ÄďBreiman convergence of the `őĹ`-term `(1/n) log őĹ(P‚āô)`. Those are the genuine
Mathlib-scale gaps recorded as the BLOCKED leaves in `ManeLowerBound`. N-L1-RN ‚ÄĒ the martingale
density step in isolation ‚ÄĒ is *not* among them, and is closed here.

## References

* Maryam Contractor, *The Pesin Entropy Formula*, UChicago REU 2023, ¬ß7 (Prop. 7.7).
* R. Ma√Ī√©, *A proof of Pesin's formula*, Ergodic Theory Dynam. Systems **1** (1981) 95‚Äď102.
-/

open MeasureTheory Filter Topology

namespace Frontier.Issue4Pesin

section Martingale

variable {ő© : Type*} {m0 : MeasurableSpace ő©} {őĹ : Measure ő©} [IsFiniteMeasure őĹ]
    {‚ĄĪ : Filtration ‚Ąē m0} {g : ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ}

/-- **The conditional-density martingale converges a.e. (martingale half of N-L1-RN).**

For a finite base measure `őĹ`, a filtration `‚ĄĪ : Filtration ‚Ąē m0`, and an integrable density
`g` measurable with respect to the limit ŌÉ-algebra `‚®Ü n, ‚ĄĪ n`, the sequence of conditional
expectations `(őĹ[g | ‚ĄĪ n]) x` converges `őĹ`-a.e. to `g x`. This is exactly the a.e. convergence of
the Ma√Ī√© conditional-density ratio `r_n = őľ(P‚āô)/őĹ(P‚āô) = (őĹ[dőľ/dőĹ | ‚ĄĪ n])` once `P‚āô` is replaced by
the abstract filtration `‚ĄĪ` it generates and `dőľ/dőĹ` by `g`.

It is a direct specialisation of Mathlib's L¬Ļ-martingale-convergence theorem
`MeasureTheory.Integrable.tendsto_ae_condExp`; it needs **no foliation data**. -/
theorem condExp_tendsto_ae (hg : Integrable g őĹ) (hgmeas : StronglyMeasurable[‚®Ü n, ‚ĄĪ n] g) :
    ‚ąÄŠĶź x ‚ąāőĹ, Tendsto (fun n => (őĹ[g | ‚ĄĪ n]) x) atTop (ūĚďĚ (g x)) :=
  hg.tendsto_ae_condExp hgmeas

/-- **Node N-L1-RN, the full Layer-1 building block: the log conditional-density rate vanishes a.e.**

For a finite base measure `őĹ`, a filtration `‚ĄĪ`, and an integrable, `‚®Ü n, ‚ĄĪ n`-measurable density
`g` that is `őĹ`-a.e. **strictly positive**, the normalised logarithm of the conditional-density
martingale tends to `0` a.e.:
`(1/n) ¬∑ log ((őĹ[g | ‚ĄĪ n]) x) ‚Üí 0`  for `őĹ`-a.e. `x`.

This is precisely the term Ma√Ī√© discards in Prop. 7.7, step 3:
`(1/n) log (őľ(P‚āô(x)) / őĹ(P‚āô(x))) ‚Üí 0` a.e., with `őľ(P‚āô)/őĹ(P‚āô) = (őĹ[dőľ/dőĹ | ‚ĄĪ n])` and `g = dőľ/dőĹ`
(strictly positive `őĹ`-a.e. since `őľ ‚Č™ őĹ` with density `g`). The proof composes:
* the a.e. martingale convergence `condExp_tendsto_ae` (`(őĹ[g|‚ĄĪ n]) x ‚Üí g x`, a finite limit), with
* the already-landed real-analytic tail `rate_log_div_tendsto_zero_of_tendsto_pos`
  (`r‚āô ‚Üí k > 0 ‚üĻ (1/n) log r‚āô ‚Üí 0`),
fed pointwise on the a.e. set where both the convergence holds and `g x > 0`.

Fully sorry-free and foliation-free: the only dynamical/geometric data is hidden inside `‚ĄĪ` (the
partition-generated filtration), `őĹ` (the leaf measure), and `g` (the Radon‚ÄďNikodym density), each
of which is an *input* a future Ma√Ī√© proof supplies ‚ÄĒ none is constructed here, and none is needed
to state or prove this node. -/
theorem condDensity_log_rate_tendsto_zero (hg : Integrable g őĹ)
    (hgmeas : StronglyMeasurable[‚®Ü n, ‚ĄĪ n] g) (hgpos : ‚ąÄŠĶź x ‚ąāőĹ, 0 < g x) :
    ‚ąÄŠĶź x ‚ąāőĹ, Tendsto (fun n : ‚Ąē => (1 / (n : ‚ĄĚ)) * Real.log ((őĹ[g | ‚ĄĪ n]) x))
      atTop (ūĚďĚ 0) := by
  filter_upwards [condExp_tendsto_ae hg hgmeas, hgpos] with x hx hxpos
  exact rate_log_div_tendsto_zero_of_tendsto_pos hxpos hx

end Martingale

end Frontier.Issue4Pesin
